Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.11,0:01:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to the start of the Pacific War, in October 1941,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.94,0:01:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a meeting to discuss the Southern Operations was held at the Army War College for several days.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.18,0:01:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Among the Southern Operations,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.66,0:01:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the leading role for the Philippine operation was the 14th Army
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:01:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,under the command of Lieutenant General Masaharu Homma,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.27,0:02:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to which the 5th Flight Group was assigned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.54,0:02:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,However, there was an important problem with the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.14,0:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was unclear if the US military would fight in the capital, Manila, or stay in the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The mission of the 14th Army is to destroy the major enemy bases in the Philippines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.49,0:02:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That means the city of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.52,0:02:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I want the 14th Army's main force to land 10 day after the start of the war and occupy the city of Manila 35 days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the plan is that the 48th Division and the 5th Flight Group
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,will be diverted to Operation Java-Malayan after a pause.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.85,0:02:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that time will be a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the purpose of the Philippine operation to capture the city of Manila or to destroy enemy troops?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.10,0:02:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to clarify it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.80,0:03:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that the enemy is likely to escape to the Bataan Peninsula, as it did during the American-Spanish War.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.08,0:03:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If the enemy can escape to the Bataan Peninsula, it will be difficult to destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.52,0:03:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, if the 48th Division and the 5th Flight Group were later pulled out by Operation Java-Malayan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.75,0:03:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,our troops would be thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.75,0:03:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bataan Peninsula is a natural fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.75,0:03:17.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be difficult if they escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.09,0:03:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should also consider fighting in Bataan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.91,0:03:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't think it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is mainly the militia, and MacArthur must be thinking of a defensive operation in Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.21,0:03:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,After the Philippine Operation, the Java Operation is planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.74,0:03:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, in order to send the 48th Division to Java,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.71,0:03:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.60,0:03:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula, I think it should be dealt with slowly later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.12,0:03:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,On November 3rd, the Chief of Staff, General Sugiyama, submitted a draft of this operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.37,0:04:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the purpose of the operation: to destroy the enemy in the Philippines and destroy its main base.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.90,0:04:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Second operational purpose: The Army, in cooperation with the Navy, will land on Luzon and quickly capture Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.19,0:04:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it necessary to write down what happens when the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.48,0:04:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The authority to make that decision is left to the commander of the 14th Army. I think you don't have to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.07,0:04:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Battle of Bataan and Corregidor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On December 8th, the 11th Air Fleet's formation of Mitsubishi G4M Zero fighters,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,informed by the successful surprise attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.36,0:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ambushed the US Air Force bases in the Philippines: Clark Air Base and Iva.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It destroyed about 100 US planes waiting on the ground and the US Air force in the Philippines was destroyed in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.49,0:05:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Subsequently, the main force under the command of the 14th Army Commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.22,0:05:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant General Masaharu Homma, formed a convoy of 76 ships
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.98,0:05:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and was escorted by the Third Fleet under the command of Vice Admiral Takahashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.73,0:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and went south into the southern waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.18,0:05:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the plan on the day of the landing, a successful landing is the first priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.39,0:05:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Its okay. The soldiers are enthusiastic and are competing for the first ride in Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.75,0:05:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Morale is quite strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,However, MacArthur must be fully prepared and waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.15,0:05:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is Bataan,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.30,0:05:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can think about it at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.11,0:05:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir, we have to take Manila all at once and not give the enemy time to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.35,0:06:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The 14th Army's main force split into two and landed in the Lingayen Gulf on December 22nd,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and in Lamon Bay on December 24th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.40,0:06:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,From the south and north, they launched their march towards the City of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.98,0:06:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.37,0:06:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn back!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.68,0:07:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The US army could not fight against the tremendous advance of the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy forces in the Central region are estimated to be 5 divisions, and 3 of them have already been devastated.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.34,0:07:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the situation of the enemy army in Manila?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.34,0:07:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know the exact situation, but some of them have been hit hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.35,0:07:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wonder if the enemy is staying in Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.04,0:07:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Although just a part of their force, enemies near Iba are retreating to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.56,0:07:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, are they going to stay on the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.04,0:07:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The advance of the Japanese army was narrowed down to Manila from the north and south,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.62,0:08:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fall of Manila seemed to be just a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.56,0:08:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,General Douglas MacArthur, commander of the United States Army Forces of the Far East,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.67,0:08:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is now faced with an important strategic decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.74,0:08:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The advance of the Japanese army is faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.64,0:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy is supported by a powerful air force and equipped with a large number of tanks and field artillery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.16,0:09:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Make Manila an open city and withdraw all troops to the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.86,0:09:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's War Plan Orange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Move the military headquarters to Corregidor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.06,0:09:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Defend here until the rescue army comes from our home country.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.36,0:09:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We can absolutely protect the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.90,0:09:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if San Fernando, the entrance to the Bataan Peninsula, is captured, our withdrawal is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.94,0:09:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No quarter given.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.36,0:09:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the Japanese here until the withdrawal is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do it in honor of the US military.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.34,0:09:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Manila is declared an open city and General MacArthur plans to blow up the bridge at 6 AM on January 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.82,0:09:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His entire army is ordered to withdrawal by then.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.28,0:10:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,All US military facilities in Manila were burned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.72,0:10:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,"Open City". In other words, a cloth was put on it to indicate that the city was defenseless,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.54,0:10:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and a truck full of soldiers, weapons, and ammunition passed by it in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.08,0:10:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, the enemy has escaped to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.90,0:10:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The 48th Division Commander strongly advises us not to let the enemy escape to the Bataan Peninsula,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.61,0:10:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and to put Manila behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.00,0:10:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Report from the reconnaissance aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.70,0:10:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Large units of enemies are retreating to the Bataan Peninsula one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.35,0:10:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, it seems that they are moving from the direction of Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.37,0:10:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's bad. There is no point in robbing Manila, which has become vacant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.32,0:10:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the enemy is also desperately fighting back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.99,0:10:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It will not easy to withdraw to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.80,0:11:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it is a clear withdrawal. We should destroy the bridge, prevent their retreat, and hit the Luzon Plain all at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.85,0:11:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it may be a trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.85,0:11:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention of the Imperial Headquarters is to defeat the enemy and quickly capture Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.78,0:11:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,48th Division must defeat their enemies and move towards Manila at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.22,0:11:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For some time, it was what was expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.90,0:11:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant General Homma thought to disobey for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.88,0:11:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but kept the duty of all military personnel to obey the orders of his superiors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.41,0:11:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and aimed at Manila as instructed by the Imperial Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.48,0:11:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This allowed the US military to safely withdrew to the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.30,0:12:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,On January 2nd, Manila fell and Japanese troops entered,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.76,0:12:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but this did not end the Philippine operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.66,0:12:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because most of the US troops stood on the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.18,0:12:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to completely occupy and secure Manila City, it is necessary to secure Manila Bay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to secure Manila Bay, the US troops on the Bataan Peninsula and Corregidor Island must be conquered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.36,0:12:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, Bataan must fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.39,0:13:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.61,0:13:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bataan Peninsula is 48km long and 24km wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.40,0:13:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The west and south were protected by cliffs, inaccessible from the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.84,0:13:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the entire peninsula was covered in jungle. It was a natural fortress.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.20,0:13:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the number of US troops was more than 80,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.48,0:14:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. We wont be defeated for three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.24,0:14:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.96,0:14:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The 48th Division was transferred to Operation Java as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.51,0:15:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,3000 soldiers of the 65th Brigade, under the command of Lieutenant General Nara,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,landed on the Lingayen Gulf on January 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They had no time to rest
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.62,0:15:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and relied On an inaccurate 1 / 200,000 scale map to pursue enemies on the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.56,0:15:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese did not see General MacArthur's withdrawal from Bataan as a strategic retreat, but as a mere rout.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.61,0:15:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese troops underestimated the US troops who retreated to the Bataan Peninsula,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and were hit harder than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 8th, Commander of the 14th Army, Lieutenant General Homma, gathered his staff members
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.92,0:15:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and held a planning meeting On measures to carry out the operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.30,0:15:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We are now in a critical phase.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.96,0:16:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is whether to continue the attack or suspend it and rebuild our formations.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.10,0:16:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to hear your opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.06,0:16:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack should continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.57,0:16:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.20,0:16:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,With the current combat power, it will only be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.07,0:16:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.31,0:16:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Until now, the operations have been left to each unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.07,0:16:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but from now on, command will be unified at military headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.90,0:16:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It we focus your attacks on the east and west coasts, you will always succeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.06,0:16:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Attack is the best defense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If we continue to attack even with a part of our forces
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and replenish our troops in the meantime, we can go on the offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.78,0:16:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the soldiers are exhausted and their damage is great.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.18,0:16:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It is better to take measures to wait for our troops to recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Opinions were divided into two camps, and there was a fierce controversy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.36,0:16:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,forcing the commander to make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.82,0:16:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 10th,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.50,0:16:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the commander made a decision and telegraphed the General Staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.28,0:16:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The attack was stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.56,0:16:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The soldiers are over the limit of their physical strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.78,0:17:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand fighting like this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.62,0:17:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I dare to be ashamed as a military commander and ask for reinforcements in this section.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,However, at the General Staff Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.09,0:17:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the 14th Army doing? It's an army of shame. The attack should continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.59,0:17:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is that the Southern operation is going well,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.44,0:17:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,only the Philippines are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.34,0:17:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Southern Expeditionary Army commander also wants an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.94,0:17:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it necessary to write about the case when the enemy escapes to the Bataan Peninsula?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.10,0:17:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The authority to make that decision is left to the commander of the 14th Army, I think you don't have to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.66,0:17:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the General Staff Headquarters who advocated the primary objective of capturing Manila,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.17,0:17:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Southern Expeditionary Army Command, who was in command.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.20,0:17:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But now the commander's decision hasn't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.75,0:17:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A week later, Lieutenant General Homma telegraphed the commander of the Southern Expeditionary Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.06,0:18:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The message was still to stop the attack and ask for reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.08,0:18:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, the Southern Expeditionary Army command dismissed several staff members,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.95,0:18:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,including the Chief of Staff of the 14th Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Several members of the General Staff Operations Division were newly incorporated into the 14th Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.92,0:18:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and an operation for a second total attack on the Bataan Peninsula was planned for.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.66,0:18:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A truck road was also built in the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.56,0:18:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,30,000 reinforcements, mainly from the 4th Division, have also arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.50,0:18:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The night before the second all out attack was a quiet one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.80,0:18:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,#POSSIBLY MISSING {Does not seem like this is the same line as before but HA continues that line to here}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.80,0:19:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well-trained soldiers slept confidently and comfortably.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.45,0:19:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,#POSSIBLY MISSING {Does not seem like this is the same line as before but HA continues that line to here}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.25,0:19:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The following day, April 3rd, the second all out attack on the Bataan Peninsula began.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.10,0:20:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.22,0:21:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,On April 9th, the US military on the Bataan Peninsula was finally defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of POWs was 70,000. Many were thin because of hunger and malaria.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All that remains is just to attack the enemy on Corregidor Island,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.81,0:21:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but that requires transporting 70,000 POWs rearwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the POWs Are sick with malaria, or malnourished.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.22,0:21:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why, if we leave them alone as they are, they will be wiped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.58,0:21:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If we transport them to the rear, there are field hospitals.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.06,0:21:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to set up a first aid station every few kilometers and deliver them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.53,0:21:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the number of POWs is 70,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.52,0:21:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Collect as many trucks as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.84,0:21:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I am doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.99,0:21:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.40,0:21:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,However, despite the commander's order, there were few Japanese trucks and it was difficult to procure them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.86,0:22:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the POWs had to walk 88km on the hot road.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.74,0:22:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 2,300 POWs died in the Bataan Death March, but this was far less than if they were left on the Bataan Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the US still called this a "death march."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.96,0:22:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Already, General MacArthur had transferred command to Major General Wainwright
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.61,0:22:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and had escaped from Corregidor Island to Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.00,0:22:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The words "I shall return", which included a counterattack against the Philippines, made the Allied side excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.36,0:22:56.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to the Bataan Peninsula is Corregidor Island, but the US military was no longer willing to resist, and on May 6th
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.49,0:23:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Corregidor Island also fell, and the Philippine campaign was completed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.36,0:23:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,However, shortly afterwards, the commander of the 14th Army was transferred to a reserve role.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.06,0:23:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The commander obeyed the orders of the Imperial Headquarters and captured Manila.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.20,0:23:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinking of the hardships of his subordinates,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.79,0:23:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he abandoned his pride as a military commander and sought reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.63,0:23:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He moved the Bataan prisoners to Corregidor to avoid useless deaths and injuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.08,0:23:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.42,0:23:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the commander's weak decisions made on the harsh battlefield were seen as a fatal flaw in a commander.
